  "prompt": "What is Stanford football record?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, the Stanford Cardinal football team has a long and storied history in college football. Here's a general overview:\n\n### **All-Time Record**\n- **Wins:** Approximately 700+\n- **Losses:** Approximately 500+\n- **Ties:** A small number (ties are rare in modern college football)\n\n*Note: These numbers are approximate and include all games since the program's inception in the late 19th century.*\n\n### **Recent Performance**\nFor the **2023 season**, Stanford's performance can vary as the season progresses. Up to October 2023, the team's record might reflect several wins and losses based on their schedule within the Pac-12 Conference and any non-conference games they have played.\n\n### **Achievements**\n- **National Championships:** Stanford has claimed multiple national titles, especially prominent during the mid-20th century.\n- **Conference Titles:** Numerous Pac-12 (formerly Pac-10) championships.\n- **Bowl Games:** Regular appearances in major bowl games, including the Rose Bowl.\n\n### **Notable Players and Coaches**\nStanford has produced numerous NFL players and notable coaches who have contributed significantly to both college and professional football.\n\n### **For the Most Up-to-Date Information**\nTo get the latest and most accurate record for the current season, including game results, rankings, and statistics, I recommend visiting the following sources:\n- **[Stanford Cardinal Official Athletics Website](https://gostanford.com/sports/football)**\n- **[ESPN Stanford Football Page](https://www.espn.com/college-football/team/_/id/346/stanford-cardinal)**\n- **[Sports Reference \u2013 College Football](https://www.sports-reference.com/cfb/schools/stanford/)**\n  \nThese platforms provide real-time updates, detailed statistics, and comprehensive coverage of Stanford's football performance throughout the season.",
